            <p>The Statue of Liberty has the status of a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and
                as a statue that contains philosophical values ​​in the form of independence, and freedom from pressure.
                The height of the Statue of Liberty, New York is 93 meters, and one of the sculptors of the Statue of Liberty is a figure
                who designed the Eiffel Tower, namely Gustave Eiffel. As for another sculptor of the Statue of Liberty named Frederic Auguste Bartholdi.
                The Statue of Liberty is a bronze statue given by France to America.
                The gift is a sign of long-standing cooperation, as well as to commemorate the 100th anniversary of America's independence.
                As for the Statue of Liberty, New York was inaugurated on October 28, 1886.    
            </p>
            
